◆ SearchSignature

using souffle::SearchSignature = typedef uint64_t

search signature of a RAM operation; each bit represents an attribute of a relation.

A one represents that the attribute has an assigned value; a zero represents that no value exists (i.e. attribute is unbounded) in the search.

84  std::vector<unsigned int> possibilities = todoStack.top();
85  todoStack.pop();
86  if (possibilities.empty()) {
87  // no more possibilities at this point, so undo our last move
88 
89  if (currentIdx == 0) {
90  // already at starting position, so no more permutations possible
91  break;
92  }
93 
94  currentIdx--;
95  seen[currentPermutation[currentIdx]] = 0;
96  currentPermutation.pop_back();
97 
98  // continue looking for permutations
99  continue;
100  }
101 
102  // try the next possibility
103  unsigned int nextNum = possibilities[0];
104 
105  // update the possibility vector for the current position
106  possibilities.erase(possibilities.begin());
107  todoStack.push(possibilities);
108 
109  if (seen[nextNum] != 0u) {
110  // number already seen in this permutation
111  continue;
112  } else {
113  // number can be used
114  seen[nextNum] = 1;
115  currentPermutation.push_back(nextNum);
116  currentIdx++;
117 
118  // if we havent reached the end of the permutation,
119  // push up the valid moves for the next position
120  if (currentIdx < clauseSize) {
121  todoStack.push(validMoves[currentIdx]);
122  }
123  }
124  }
125 
126  // found all permutations
127  return permutations;
128 }

◆ formNegatedLiterals()

std::vector<std::vector<AstLiteral*> > souffle::formNegatedLiterals ( AstProgram &  program,
AstAtom *  atom 
)

Forms the bodies that will replace the negation of a given inlined atom.

E.g. a(x) <- (a11(x), a12(x)) ; (a21(x), a22(x)) => !a(x) <- (!a11(x), !a21(x)) ; (!a11(x), !a22(x)) ; ... Essentially, produce every combination (m_1 ^ m_2 ^ ...) where m_i is the negation of a literal in the ith rule of a.

Returns a list of clauses that should replace the given clause after one step of inlining.

If no inlining can occur, the list will only contain a clone of the original clause.

◆ getInlinedLiteral()

NullableVector< std::vector< AstLiteral * > > souffle::getInlinedLiteral ( AstProgram &  program,
AstLiteral *  lit 
)

Tries to perform a single step of inlining on the given literal.

Returns a pair of nullable vectors (v, w) such that:

  • v is valid if and only if the literal can be directly inlined, whereby it contains the bodies that replace it
  • if v is not valid, then w is valid if and only if the literal cannot be inlined directly, but contains a subargument that can be. In this case, it will contain the versions that will replace it.
  • If both are invalid, then no more inlining can occur on this literal and we are done.

Returns a SIPS function based on the SIPS option provided.

The SIPS function will return the index of the appropriate atom in a clause given a goal.

E.g. the 'max-bound' SIPS function will return the atom in the clause with the maximum number of bound arguments.

505  AstTranslator().translateUnit(*astTranslationUnit);

524  std::make_unique<ParallelTransformer>()),
525  std::make_unique<ReportIndexTransfomer>());
526 
527  ramTransform->apply(*ramTranslationUnit);
528  if (ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport().getNumIssues() != 0) {
529  std::cerr << ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport();
530  }
531 
532  // Output the transformed RAM program and return
533  if (Global::config().get("show") == "transformed-ram") {
534  std::cout << ramTranslationUnit->getProgram();
535  return 0;
536  }
537 
538  try {
539  if (!Global::config().has("compile") && !Global::config().has("dl-program") &&
540  !Global::config().has("generate") && !Global::config().has("swig")) {
541  // ------- interpreter -------------
542 
543  std::thread profiler;
544  // Start up profiler if needed
545  if (Global::config().has("live-profile") && !Global::config().has("compile")) {
546  profiler = std::thread([]() { profile::Tui().runProf(); });
547  }
548 
549  // configure and execute interpreter
550  std::unique_ptr<InterpreterEngine> interpreter(
551  std::make_unique<InterpreterEngine>(*ramTranslationUnit));
552  interpreter->executeMain();
553  // If the profiler was started, join back here once it exits.
554  if (profiler.joinable()) {
555  profiler.join();
556  }
557  if (Global::config().has("provenance")) {
558  // Test for bugged combination of provenance, interpreted souffle, and concurrency
559  if (Global::config().get("jobs") != "1") {
560  throw std::runtime_error("Provenance is not supported with parallel interpreted mode");
561  }
562 
563  // only run explain interface if interpreted
564  InterpreterProgInterface interface(*interpreter);
565  if (Global::config().get("provenance") == "explain" ||
566  Global::config().get("provenance") == "subtreeHeights") {
567  explain(interface, false, Global::config().get("provenance") == "subtreeHeights");
568  } else if (Global::config().get("provenance") == "explore") {
569  explain(interface, true, false);
570  }
571  }
572  } else {
573  // ------- compiler -------------
574  std::string compileCmd = ::findTool("souffle-compile", souffleExecutable, ".");
575  /* Fail if a souffle-compile executable is not found */
576  if (!isExecutable(compileCmd)) {
577  throw std::runtime_error("failed to locate souffle-compile");
578  }
579  compileCmd += " ";
580 
581  std::unique_ptr<Synthesiser> synthesiser = std::make_unique<Synthesiser>(*ramTranslationUnit);
582 
583  // Find the base filename for code generation and execution
584  std::string baseFilename;
585  if (Global::config().has("dl-program")) {
586  baseFilename = Global::config().get("dl-program");
587  } else if (Global::config().has("generate")) {
588  baseFilename = Global::config().get("generate");
589 
590  // trim .cpp extension if it exists
591  if (baseFilename.size() >= 4 && baseFilename.substr(baseFilename.size() - 4) == ".cpp") {
592  baseFilename = baseFilename.substr(0, baseFilename.size() - 4);
593  }
594  } else {
595  baseFilename = tempFile();
596  }
597  if (baseName(baseFilename) == "/" || baseName(baseFilename) == ".") {
598  baseFilename = tempFile();
599  }
600 
601  std::string baseIdentifier = identifier(simpleName(baseFilename));
602  std::string sourceFilename = baseFilename + ".cpp";
603 
604  bool withSharedLibrary;
605  std::ofstream os(sourceFilename);
606  synthesiser->generateCode(os, baseIdentifier, withSharedLibrary);
607  os.close();
608 
609  if (withSharedLibrary) {
610  if (!Global::config().has("libraries")) {
611  Global::config().set("libraries", "functors");
612  }
613  if (!Global::config().has("library-dir")) {
614  Global::config().set("library-dir", ".");
615  }
616  }
617 
618  if (Global::config().has("swig")) {
619  compileCmd += "-s " + Global::config().get("swig") + " ";
620  compileToBinary(compileCmd, sourceFilename);
621  } else if (Global::config().has("compile")) {
622  auto start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
623  compileToBinary(compileCmd, sourceFilename);
624  /* Report overall run-time in verbose mode */
625  if (Global::config().has("verbose")) {
626  auto end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
627  std::cout << "Compilation Time: " << std::chrono::duration<double>(end - start).count()
628  << "sec\n";
629  }
630  // run compiled C++ program if requested.
631  if (!Global::config().has("dl-program") && !Global::config().has("swig")) {
632  executeBinary(baseFilename);
633  }
634  }
635  }
636  } catch (std::exception& e) {
637  std::cerr << e.what() << std::endl;
638  std::exit(1);
639  }
640 
641  /* Report overall run-time in verbose mode */
642  if (Global::config().has("verbose")) {
643  auto souffle_end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
644  std::cout << "Total Time: " << std::chrono::duration<double>(souffle_end - souffle_start).count()
645  << "sec\n";
646  }
647 
648  return 0;
649 }

const std::vector< unsigned int > &  newOrder 
)

Reorders the atoms of a clause to be in the given order.

Remaining body literals remain in the same order.

E.g. if atoms are [a,b,c] and given order is [1,2,0], then the final atom order will be [b,c,a].

Parameters
clauseclause to reorder atoms in
newOrdernew order of atoms; atoms[i] = atoms[newOrder[i]]
